‘Women Don’t Need a Fight to Have a Choice’

Ireland banned abortion in the 1980’s and the first abortion in the country was completed last year following death threats made on a letter sent to the woman’s home regarding her unborn child. The European Court of Human Rights ruled in a case (HRC v The Irish Republic) that, although pregnant women could go to England for an abortion that is legal in Britain, Ireland’s ban went beyond what was permitted. The Irish Countrywomen’s Association, a pro-life women’s group in Ireland, want to give the government time to catch up with opinion in Ireland and championed the call for the referendum in an attempt to ensure that, if repealed, abortion would be declared illegal but they now believe that making abortion illegal is a better outcome, according to The Times.
